WEBVTT

00:01.830 --> 00:03.932
Okay, Emma, let's get these little piggies

00:03.934 --> 00:06.302
into this little pink sparkly market, okay?

00:06.304 --> 00:09.038
Oh, come on, these are too small too.

00:09.040 --> 00:12.281
Hey, if you're not careful,
you're going to be all feet and no head.

00:13.442 --> 00:15.278
Riley was supposed to
take her shoe shopping.

00:15.378 --> 00:17.546
You guys know where she's
been the last couple of days?

00:17.546 --> 00:19.212
I don't know. How should I know?

00:19.312 --> 00:20.436
Don't look at me. I haven't seen her.

00:20.536 --> 00:24.207
Now if you'll excuse me,
my girlfriend's waiting for her coffee.

00:24.207 --> 00:25.408
What's up with him?

00:25.408 --> 00:27.310
What? What? Oh, who, Danny?

00:27.310 --> 00:29.445
Danny? Uh, no, him and Riley had a thing.

00:29.445 --> 00:31.347
You know?
He said something, she said something back.

00:31.347 --> 00:34.150
That pretty much clears it up, right?

00:34.150 --> 00:36.919
I have amazing news!

00:36.919 --> 00:40.857
Evelyn is dead!

00:40.857 --> 00:41.458
What?

00:41.483 --> 00:43.860
Wait, you mean the sweet
old lady across the hall?

00:43.860 --> 00:45.027
Sweet? Please.

00:45.027 --> 00:47.397
Right now she's slow dancing with Satan.

00:50.066 --> 00:53.035
And I am going to pry the
listing for that apartment

00:53.035 --> 00:56.172
out of her cold, gnarled fingers.

00:56.172 --> 00:58.941
Well, I loved Evelyn.

00:58.941 --> 01:01.444
I mean, she used to let me
wonder around her apartment

01:01.444 --> 01:04.513
and put blue stickers on stuff
I could have after she died.

01:05.848 --> 01:07.518
I put stickers all over that place.

01:07.618 --> 01:10.588
I'm gonna be stickin' rich!

01:10.588 --> 01:12.056
You're a horrible person.

01:12.056 --> 01:15.059
Oh, okay, whatever you say,
realtor to the dead.

01:15.059 --> 01:16.227
- Oh.
- Yeah.

01:16.227 --> 01:17.561
Can't we just agree

01:17.561 --> 01:20.631
you're both tied in the
horrible department?

01:20.631 --> 01:23.014
How could Riley ignore a
text about shoe shopping?

01:23.114 --> 01:26.651
God, I hope nothing's wrong.
Where the heck is she?

01:27.319 --> 01:29.354
So what do we think?

01:29.354 --> 01:32.490
Can we maybe get up and
put some clothes on today?

01:32.490 --> 01:35.760
Can I bring you a mirror and
show you what's going on here?

01:35.760 --> 01:38.430
Mom, what's the point?

01:38.430 --> 01:41.433
You know, I'd rather just stay
here where no one can see me

01:41.433 --> 01:43.001
and I can't ruin any more lives.

01:43.001 --> 01:44.636
Just mine, honey.

01:44.636 --> 01:47.249
I ruined everything with Ben and Danny.

01:47.349 --> 01:49.384
Oh my God! I thought you were gonna

01:49.384 --> 01:51.353
tell me you were pregnant...

01:51.353 --> 01:53.021
And by a Wheeler!

01:53.021 --> 01:57.092
Mom, I destroyed the relationship

01:57.092 --> 01:59.361
I waited my whole life for with Ben,

01:59.361 --> 02:01.863
and then I ruined the best
friendship I ever had with Danny

02:01.863 --> 02:04.866
by telling him I think
I'm in love with him?

02:04.866 --> 02:08.603
Oh, there's something new and disturbing.

02:08.603 --> 02:11.693
Why don't you go to your apartment
and call me? We can talk about it.

02:11.793 --> 02:14.762
I'm sort of turning this
into a crafting room.

02:14.762 --> 02:17.799
I don't really have an apartment anymore.

02:17.799 --> 02:19.632
I kind of gave up my lease.

02:19.732 --> 02:21.300
What?

02:21.300 --> 02:23.736
Oh, well, okay, maybe we can just

02:23.736 --> 02:26.973
move you into the basement
with your father.

02:26.973 --> 02:31.144
Mom, I just... you know,
I need a fresh start.

02:31.144 --> 02:33.947
A life without the wheelers.
They'll be better off without me.

02:34.047 --> 02:35.515
I agree.

02:35.515 --> 02:37.404
And you know what else
you'll be better off without?

02:37.504 --> 02:39.273
That hairdo.

02:39.273 --> 02:41.308
You kind of look like a lesbian.

02:44.946 --> 02:47.915
♪ It's amazing how the unexpected ♪

02:47.915 --> 02:51.079
♪ Can take your life
and change directions ♪

02:51.179 --> 02:54.370
-- Sync and corrected by --
-- <font color="829EE0">TheDelta</font> --

02:54.889 --> 02:56.524
All right, thank you.

02:56.524 --> 02:57.825
Okay, well, Riley hasn't

02:57.825 --> 02:58.893
been to work all week,

02:58.893 --> 03:00.995
which her boss now knows.

03:00.995 --> 03:03.531
I may have gotten her in trouble.

03:03.531 --> 03:05.533
Mom, what the hell are you doing?

03:05.533 --> 03:06.534
Waiting for someone

03:06.534 --> 03:07.835
to come claim that old biddy,

03:07.835 --> 03:08.836
so I can get the listing

03:08.836 --> 03:10.838
and cash in.

03:10.838 --> 03:12.940
Ooh! It's showtime!

03:14.775 --> 03:17.278
Hello! I'm Bonnie.

03:17.278 --> 03:19.914
You must be Evelyn's beloved niece.

03:19.914 --> 03:21.015
- Granddaughter.
- Audrey.

03:21.015 --> 03:23.784
- Ashley.
- You sure? I like Audrey better.

03:23.784 --> 03:27.188
Evelyn and I were very close.

03:27.188 --> 03:28.923
I loved her like

03:28.923 --> 03:31.058
she was my own grandma.

03:31.058 --> 03:33.327
She hated you.

03:33.327 --> 03:36.330
Well, who's laughing now, Evelyn?

03:37.798 --> 03:41.002
Again, very sorry for your loss.

03:42.136 --> 03:44.105
Here's my card.

03:44.105 --> 03:45.106
Why don't you let me

03:45.106 --> 03:46.507
help you sell this place?

03:46.507 --> 03:48.142
I think we're good.

03:48.142 --> 03:50.177
Hey, ma, good news.

03:50.177 --> 03:51.412
I just heard that old lady

03:51.412 --> 03:52.446
you hated died!

03:54.882 --> 03:56.918
He's talking about my mother.

03:56.918 --> 03:59.053
Hi, I'm Ashley.

03:59.053 --> 04:00.788
Nice to meet you, Ashley.

04:03.858 --> 04:05.860
Oh my God! Danny Wheeler?

04:05.860 --> 04:07.028
I can't believe grandma never mentioned

04:07.028 --> 04:08.963
she lived across the
hall from a hockey star.

04:08.963 --> 04:11.032
Sweetie, your grandma didn't know

04:11.032 --> 04:13.301
she lived in an apartment.

04:14.535 --> 04:16.536
So are you a hockey fan?

04:16.536 --> 04:18.539
- Yeah, and a Danny Wheeler fan.
- Ah.

04:18.539 --> 04:19.906
I've never missed a game.

04:19.906 --> 04:22.009
I can tell you every
important play he's ever made.

04:22.009 --> 04:24.078
Well, that won't take too long.

04:24.078 --> 04:25.947
How about I make you a deal?

04:25.947 --> 04:28.816
You hook me up with this place

04:28.816 --> 04:30.051
and I'll hook you up

04:30.051 --> 04:31.385
with that face.

04:33.955 --> 04:35.790
Danny?

04:35.790 --> 04:37.959
Danny,
you need to go on a date with that girl

04:37.959 --> 04:40.561
and convince her to give me
the listing to that apartment.

04:40.561 --> 04:43.197
Great, just let me go tell my girlfriend.

04:43.197 --> 04:45.933
Thanks, sweetie. You're a good son.

04:45.933 --> 04:48.970
Mom, I'm not going to break
up with Robyn for you.

04:48.970 --> 04:50.271
Why not?

04:50.271 --> 04:52.873
Robyn is not the right girl for you.

04:52.873 --> 04:56.811
We have nothing in common,
and she never laughs at my jokes.

04:56.811 --> 04:59.480
Neither do I. Maybe you
and I should break up.

05:04.118 --> 05:05.987
Ooh, Ashley!

05:05.987 --> 05:07.788
So you thought things over?

05:07.788 --> 05:10.338
Actually, I'm looking for Tucker Dobbs.

05:10.438 --> 05:12.173
My grandma left something for him.

05:12.173 --> 05:13.210
Oh, I don't think that he's even...

05:13.310 --> 05:15.178
I'm here, I'm here! I'm home, I'm home!

05:15.178 --> 05:19.178
Oh God! I am so sorry. Poor Evelyn.

05:19.316 --> 05:22.586
I... I'm gonna miss her so much.

05:22.586 --> 05:25.322
You know, she was just such a
bright light in my dark...

05:25.322 --> 05:28.191
a shoe box?

05:28.191 --> 05:31.695
Okay,
unless that thing has three mink coats,

05:31.695 --> 05:33.864
two Tiffany lamps,
and an antique vanity mirror,

05:33.864 --> 05:36.333
me and you about to have some words.

05:36.333 --> 05:38.735
Who are you people?

05:40.410 --> 05:42.912
Oh! Nice work.

05:42.912 --> 05:45.849
Could you possibly be any more selfish?

05:45.849 --> 05:48.885
Ooh, is there any chance that
she left you the apartment?

05:48.885 --> 05:50.987
If so, I'd love to represent you.

05:53.123 --> 05:56.660
Oh, hell to the no!

05:58.161 --> 06:01.398
I didn't even put a sticker on this thing.

06:01.953 --> 06:03.855
Oh, my God, wait.
There's something inside of it.

06:03.855 --> 06:05.823
Maybe a key to a safety-deposit box.

06:07.191 --> 06:09.709
Ah, crap. Nothing.

06:11.763 --> 06:13.110
Wait.

06:13.210 --> 06:15.412
Wait, what's this?

06:15.412 --> 06:17.481
"My dear Tucker,

06:17.481 --> 06:19.650
"thank you for making my
final days on this earth

06:19.650 --> 06:22.719
"the best days of my life.

06:22.719 --> 06:25.355
"You were the grandson I never had."

06:27.791 --> 06:30.605
Oh, Evelyn, they took you too soon.

06:32.659 --> 06:34.268
"P.S.,

06:34.353 --> 06:36.021
"tell Bonnie I hate her."

06:36.021 --> 06:38.023
What?

06:38.023 --> 06:41.226
Oh, my God. I just got off the
phone with Riley's landlord.

06:41.226 --> 06:43.228
She gave up her apartment.
She moved back to Jersey.

06:43.228 --> 06:46.699
Nobody moves back to Jersey!

06:50.619 --> 06:52.354
Well, well, well,

06:52.354 --> 06:54.490
if it isn't everyone's favorite delinquent.

06:54.490 --> 06:56.525
Did you come to return my lawn gnome?

06:56.525 --> 06:58.360
That was 15 years ago.

06:58.360 --> 07:00.362
He was part of a pair...

07:00.362 --> 07:02.731
Gnomeo and Juliet.

07:02.731 --> 07:04.310
Okay, well, if it gives you closure,

07:04.410 --> 07:05.978
Gnomeo didn't suffer.

07:05.978 --> 07:07.913
He also didn't float. Is Riley home?

07:07.913 --> 07:09.915
- No!
- Mrs. perrin, please!

07:09.915 --> 07:12.351
Please, I need to talk to her.
I need to know what's wrong.

07:12.351 --> 07:14.153
Really? Haven't you done enough?

07:14.153 --> 07:16.422
No, wait. Haven't I done enough?

07:16.422 --> 07:17.990
Am I why she ran away?

07:17.990 --> 07:18.983
Mrs. perrin!

07:19.083 --> 07:21.219
Please talk to me.

07:26.424 --> 07:28.126
Come on, Danny.

07:28.126 --> 07:30.695
I'm not asking you to sleep with Ashley.

07:30.695 --> 07:32.497
Just make out with her!

07:32.497 --> 07:34.332
You know, maybe a little over-the-bra action

07:34.332 --> 07:35.733
until I get the listing.

07:35.733 --> 07:38.036
Robyn will never know.

07:38.036 --> 07:42.036
Mom,
I am not cheating on my girlfriend for you.

07:42.373 --> 07:45.210
I just did that once so you
could pass your driver's test.

07:45.210 --> 07:47.212
Never again!

07:47.212 --> 07:49.848
Miss Nussbaum still calls me.

07:54.085 --> 07:56.226
- Robyn!
- Hey, Mrs. Wheeler.

07:56.326 --> 07:57.694
Is Danny ready?

07:57.694 --> 07:58.862
Uh, Danny?

07:58.862 --> 08:01.097
Uh, sick as a dog.

08:01.097 --> 08:02.260
Yeah, in bed.

08:02.360 --> 08:05.863
Pretty serious cold-flu-strep-

08:05.863 --> 08:08.399
phlegmy-stomach-head thingy.

08:08.399 --> 08:10.233
That's horrible. Why didn't he call me?

08:10.333 --> 08:12.468
Uh, because he was too
busy calling the doctor,

08:12.468 --> 08:14.003
the drugstore, and his mother.

08:14.003 --> 08:16.205
Jeez, you are very self-centered.

08:16.205 --> 08:18.274
Yeah, all right,
he will get to you when he can,

08:18.274 --> 08:19.976
- or not, okay?
- Okay.

08:19.976 --> 08:22.511
- Well, tell him if he needs...
- Bye, bye, bye, bye!

08:22.511 --> 08:23.580
Hey, is that Robyn?

08:23.680 --> 08:25.748
Uh, Robyn? Yes.

08:25.748 --> 08:27.484
Yes, it was.

08:27.484 --> 08:31.221
Um, but she got an emergency
phone call from the courthouse.

08:31.221 --> 08:33.789
Either it was a motion she forgot to file

08:33.889 --> 08:35.524
or a file she forgot to motion.

08:35.524 --> 08:39.361
I wasn't really paying attention.
She's very dull.

08:39.361 --> 08:41.395
Wow, so she's standing me up?

08:41.395 --> 08:43.465
I didn't think of that.

08:43.465 --> 08:47.502
Yes. Yes, she is.
You should break up with her!

08:47.502 --> 08:50.639
Oh, Ashley! Huh?

08:50.639 --> 08:53.308
Got a little dinner there? Eating alone?

08:53.308 --> 08:56.511
Sad little to-go box.
Maybe Danny can join you?

08:56.511 --> 08:59.748
These are my grandma's ashes.

08:59.748 --> 09:01.688
Oh. Do you need a hug?

09:01.788 --> 09:03.957
Danny, take your shirt off.

09:03.957 --> 09:06.126
Mom!

09:06.126 --> 09:08.458
Look, Ashley, I'm sorry. You seem...

09:08.558 --> 09:10.293
mom!

09:10.293 --> 09:11.861
You seem like a really nice person,

09:11.861 --> 09:15.131
but I have a girlfriend who
my mom does not approve of.

09:15.131 --> 09:17.267
But you know what?
I don't need her approval.

09:17.267 --> 09:19.269
Right, mom?

09:19.269 --> 09:20.670
Damn.

