09:29.113 --> 09:31.281
Ben. Oh, my God.

09:31.281 --> 09:33.651
Ben, what are you doing here?

09:33.651 --> 09:36.153
I'm not allowed to have boys over.

09:36.153 --> 09:37.892
Riley, you can't run away from home.

09:37.992 --> 09:40.461
Well, run away to home... from your home.

09:40.461 --> 09:43.464
Whatever. Riley, you
can't run away from me.

09:43.464 --> 09:45.332
Ben, haven't I done enough damage?

09:45.332 --> 09:48.569
- Oh!
- Oh, Ben!

09:48.569 --> 09:50.971
You have now!

09:50.971 --> 09:53.574
You okay?

09:54.379 --> 09:56.614
Oh, honey, I'm so, so, so sorry.

09:56.614 --> 09:59.283
Are you comfy? Hungry? In pain?

09:59.283 --> 10:02.186
- Ah!
- Oh my God! Are you in pain?

10:02.186 --> 10:03.595
Well, my lawn is.

10:03.695 --> 10:05.564
The lawn is dented.

10:05.564 --> 10:08.567
You dented my lawn.

10:09.023 --> 10:11.025
No, no, no, this is all my fault.

10:11.025 --> 10:13.027
He has to spend the night.
You have to spend the night.

10:13.027 --> 10:15.029
Well, how about we put
him on the curb instead?

10:15.029 --> 10:17.164
I'd say, you know,
we could put him in a white trash bag,

10:17.164 --> 10:19.300
but that's a little redundant.

10:19.300 --> 10:22.069
Mom, could you be cool just, like, once?

10:22.069 --> 10:23.671
You're embarrassing me.

10:23.671 --> 10:27.007
Why don't you go make Ben something to eat?

10:27.007 --> 10:29.043
And I will fix up the guest bedroom for him.

10:29.043 --> 10:32.379
Fine. But if I wake up and
that cat is shaved again,

10:32.379 --> 10:34.982
there will be hell to pay!

10:34.982 --> 10:36.610
I didn't shave that cat.

10:37.525 --> 10:39.560
I waxed it.

10:41.262 --> 10:43.798
Riley, why are you here?

10:43.798 --> 10:45.833
Did you come home because
of what happened between us?

10:45.833 --> 10:48.602
Ben, I really,
I just... I don't want to talk about it.

10:48.602 --> 10:52.673
- Well...
- And please don't touch my beanie babies.

11:01.316 --> 11:03.118
- Hello?
- Danny, hey.

11:03.118 --> 11:05.420
Look, we have a situation.
I need you to ask mom to watch Emma

11:05.420 --> 11:07.222
and get out here a.S.A.P. It's Riley.

11:07.222 --> 11:09.473
Oh. I'm pretty busy right now, Ben.

11:09.573 --> 11:12.275
Okay, whatever you guys are
fighting about right now,

11:12.275 --> 11:13.810
you need to forget it, okay?

11:13.810 --> 11:16.213
We're not fighting.
She just said something I liked

11:16.213 --> 11:18.415
and then said something I didn't like,

11:18.415 --> 11:22.085
so I said... okay, maybe we're fighting.

11:22.085 --> 11:23.553
Danny, you could...

11:26.123 --> 11:27.958
are you okay?

11:27.958 --> 11:30.827
Oh, just... yeah, I'm okay.
I was just trying so hard to walk.

11:30.827 --> 11:32.496
I don't want to be a burden to you, Riley.

11:32.496 --> 11:34.064
- I just...
- Oh, it's okay.

11:34.064 --> 11:35.265
It's okay.

11:37.268 --> 11:39.036
Ooh, ooh, here she is.

11:39.070 --> 11:40.971
Okay, I'm counting on you, Emma.

11:41.005 --> 11:42.940
Okay, you ready? Yeah. Okay.

11:42.974 --> 11:45.843
Oh, Ashley, thank God you're here.

11:45.877 --> 11:46.638
What's wrong?

11:46.663 --> 11:49.680
My son Ben is having some
kind of crisis in Jersey

11:49.714 --> 11:51.982
and he needs me,
but I can't find anybody to watch Emma.

11:52.016 --> 11:54.585
Oh, thank God. Thank you so much.
You're a real life-saver.

11:54.619 --> 11:55.786
Everything you need is right here

11:55.820 --> 11:57.721
and I shouldn't be gone for more than....

11:57.755 --> 11:59.423
So just call me if you got any problems.

11:59.457 --> 12:01.725
- I don't have your num...
- Bye bye now!

12:01.759 --> 12:04.428
Hey, mom, you know where my... oh!

12:04.462 --> 12:06.196
Ashley, um...

12:06.231 --> 12:08.165
I was just, um...

12:08.199 --> 12:10.367
Your mom made me watch her.
She just said no one was in here.

12:10.401 --> 12:12.136
I should get some pants.

12:12.170 --> 12:15.105
So can I ask you a hockey question?

12:15.140 --> 12:17.007
It's a game played on skates

12:17.041 --> 12:19.109
and the object is to get
the puck into the net.

12:19.144 --> 12:20.878
- It's kind of simple.
- No.

12:20.912 --> 12:23.046
The game against the Canucks when
you were robbed of the hat trick?

12:23.081 --> 12:25.015
That's because Horvat tripped you,
wasn't it?

12:25.049 --> 12:27.518
Yeah. Nobody saw that.

12:27.552 --> 12:28.585
I did.

12:28.620 --> 12:30.420
I see everything you do.

12:33.591 --> 12:35.526
Oh my God, you do that too?

12:35.560 --> 12:37.194
You should listen to 2C.

12:37.228 --> 12:38.228
I do.

12:38.263 --> 12:39.363
I think she's leaving Gary.

12:39.397 --> 12:40.497
Well, you know he cheatin'!

12:40.532 --> 12:43.267
With 3B!

12:43.301 --> 12:45.135
Oh, you know what? You can't go in here.

12:45.170 --> 12:46.870
Danny's with Ashley.

12:48.006 --> 12:50.007
Oh, hey, cover for me.

12:50.041 --> 12:51.074
Tucker?

12:56.748 --> 12:58.782
Ahem. If anyone asks,

12:58.816 --> 13:02.386
you have not seen me. I just need to
find somewhere to stash the ashes.

13:02.420 --> 13:04.454
Then I'm giving Evelyn
the funeral she deserves.

13:04.489 --> 13:07.591
- And the coat?
- Hey, I dot it, I got it.

13:07.625 --> 13:09.426
Hi again.

13:09.460 --> 13:11.295
I brought Danny some soup
to make him feel better.

13:11.329 --> 13:12.429
You're too late!

13:12.463 --> 13:14.464
He's, um... he's gone.

13:14.499 --> 13:16.400
What?

13:16.434 --> 13:19.002
It was just a cold!

13:19.037 --> 13:20.871
How could this happen?

13:20.905 --> 13:22.806
Not dead.

13:22.840 --> 13:25.909
He's downstairs doing laundry.

13:25.944 --> 13:27.678
Yeah, yeah, let me show you where he's at.

13:27.712 --> 13:29.846
Oh, thank God you're pretty.

13:31.616 --> 13:33.717
Ben, just let it go, please.

13:33.751 --> 13:36.486
I promise everyone will be
better off without me around.

13:36.521 --> 13:38.255
Nothing will be better without you.

13:38.289 --> 13:40.190
I ruined a perfect friendship.

13:40.225 --> 13:42.192
That's not true.
I'll never stop being your friend.

13:42.227 --> 13:43.393
Actually, I meant...

13:43.428 --> 13:45.195
look, I get it. I messed up.

13:45.230 --> 13:47.331
I pushed you away and now you
don't think we can just be friends.

13:47.365 --> 13:50.133
But we can. I can.

13:50.168 --> 13:52.236
What about Danny?

13:52.270 --> 13:53.837
What about him?

13:53.871 --> 13:55.872
You'll forget about whatever
you're fighting about.

13:55.907 --> 13:57.808
He can't survive without you.

13:57.842 --> 13:58.942
Did he say that?

13:58.977 --> 14:01.545
Yes.

14:01.579 --> 14:04.781
Of course. Totally. Riley, he needs you.

14:04.816 --> 14:07.317
Don't you know that? We all need you.

14:07.352 --> 14:09.253
Really?

14:10.521 --> 14:11.588
Okay.

14:11.623 --> 14:13.190
Okay?

14:13.224 --> 14:15.225
Okay, you'll come back?

14:15.260 --> 14:17.094
All right. Oh, come here!

14:17.128 --> 14:19.096
All right, let me pack your stuff.

14:19.130 --> 14:22.032
All right, you can stay with
us until you find something.

14:22.066 --> 14:24.134
I won't be weird, I promise.

14:25.203 --> 14:28.171
Oh my God.

14:28.206 --> 14:31.808
I'm all healed. It's a miracle.

14:33.858 --> 14:36.320
My God, I can't believe
you just lied to me.

14:36.420 --> 14:38.221
- No, Riley, I...
- No, thank you, thank you

14:38.255 --> 14:40.056
for proving that I made the right decision.

14:40.090 --> 14:40.926
What decision?

14:40.951 --> 14:44.093
There is a position open
at my firm in Buffalo.

14:44.128 --> 14:46.596
You know,
it's the other city that never sleeps.

14:46.630 --> 14:49.699
And I'm taking it. Now go away.

14:49.733 --> 14:53.603
I'll give you a 10-second head start...

14:53.637 --> 14:56.306
Then we'll find out if you float.

14:58.609 --> 15:02.245
Oh, I waxed the cat.

15:11.989 --> 15:15.124
Ah. Oh, look, Danny! Look who's here!

15:15.159 --> 15:18.161
- Oh, now who would put this here? God.
- No!

15:18.195 --> 15:19.762
What?

15:19.797 --> 15:21.998
Oh. Oh, darn it!

15:22.032 --> 15:23.062
Now we're locked in.

15:23.087 --> 15:25.535
Now why would you do that?
Can't you read?

15:25.569 --> 15:26.736
No!

15:26.770 --> 15:28.771
I can't.

15:28.806 --> 15:30.807
And now you're making me feel bad

15:30.841 --> 15:32.742
about my lack of education.

15:34.511 --> 15:38.114
And I got this scar from the Detroit game.

15:38.148 --> 15:40.083
I tripped coming out of the locker room.

15:40.117 --> 15:43.286
Okay, people,
we have an emergency situation.

15:43.320 --> 15:46.089
We need to stage a friend-ervention
and bring Riley home.

15:46.123 --> 15:48.057
Dude, why don't you just leave her alone?

15:48.092 --> 15:50.126
- I know that's my plan.
- She's leaving, Danny.

15:50.160 --> 15:52.028
She's moving to Buffalo.

15:52.062 --> 15:53.863
I tried to stop her,
but she won't listen to me.

15:53.897 --> 15:56.566
Maybe she'll listen to you. Please help me.

15:56.600 --> 15:57.734
It's not that easy.

15:57.768 --> 15:59.769
Yes, it is! She's your best friend.

15:59.803 --> 16:02.372
Oh, you should never fight with friends.

16:02.406 --> 16:04.207
Sometimes they're all you have.

16:04.241 --> 16:05.441
Yeah, what she said.

16:05.476 --> 16:07.343
And who are you?

16:07.378 --> 16:09.379
I'm Evelyn's granddaughter.

16:09.413 --> 16:13.950
Oh. She hated my mom.

16:13.984 --> 16:16.953
Any chance she had a car?

16:20.724 --> 16:22.859
Oh, I swear, I thought we would never

16:22.893 --> 16:24.794
get him back from that firehouse.

16:24.828 --> 16:28.865
You leave one kid in a basket as a joke.
You know, come on!

16:28.899 --> 16:30.533
You're hilarious.

16:30.567 --> 16:31.668
I know.

16:31.702 --> 16:34.470
Oh. You know what, Robyn?

16:34.505 --> 16:36.339
I think I was wrong about you.

16:36.373 --> 16:38.541
I didn't think you and Danny
were right for each other.

16:38.575 --> 16:41.377
Haven't been so sure either,

16:41.412 --> 16:43.379
but after hearing all
these stories about him,

16:43.414 --> 16:46.082
I really want to keep trying.
He really is special.

16:46.116 --> 16:49.886
Yep, and I've got the bus pass to prove it.

16:49.920 --> 16:51.954
Look, I'm sorry I locked you in here

16:51.989 --> 16:53.856
and tried to break you and Danny up.

16:53.891 --> 16:55.858
I just really wanted that apartment listing.

16:55.893 --> 16:58.594
What? You were trying to break us up?

16:59.930 --> 17:01.731
No.

17:01.765 --> 17:05.768
No. No, it's just...
it's one of my stories.

17:05.803 --> 17:08.371
You know? They're not all true.

17:09.606 --> 17:12.541
Oh, do you have any quarters, huh?

17:12.576 --> 17:15.310
That'd be fun, huh?

17:25.923 --> 17:27.990
- Riley!
- Ah, these are mine!

17:28.025 --> 17:29.792
Riley?

17:31.829 --> 17:34.597
Ben?

17:34.631 --> 17:35.698
What are you all doing here?

17:35.733 --> 17:36.833
You can't leave us.

17:36.867 --> 17:38.468
We won't let you.

17:38.502 --> 17:40.737
Okay? Emma needs you.
You're her role model...

17:40.771 --> 17:44.373
You know, when you're not in the
middle of a nervous breakdown.

17:44.408 --> 17:45.575
Who are you?

17:45.609 --> 17:47.343
Oh, I'm Ashley.

17:47.377 --> 17:49.479
My grandma Evelyn lived across
the hall from these guys.

17:49.513 --> 17:52.248
She's dead. I got her car.

17:52.282 --> 17:54.350
Oh, I loved Evelyn.

17:54.384 --> 17:57.920
We used to get together and
complain about Mrs. Wheeler.

17:57.955 --> 18:00.089
Focus, people.

18:00.124 --> 18:01.891
Hey, sorry I'm late.

18:01.925 --> 18:03.726
I was looking for a park for Evelyn.

18:03.761 --> 18:05.027
What are you doing with those ashes?

18:05.062 --> 18:07.630
You may not care about your grandmother,

18:07.664 --> 18:09.799
but I loved her, and she was special to me.

18:09.833 --> 18:12.635
And I'm going to give her
the burial that she deserves.

18:12.669 --> 18:13.770
That's sweet,

18:13.804 --> 18:15.605
but that's not my grandma.

18:15.639 --> 18:18.307
That's her cat, wilton.

18:18.342 --> 18:19.709
Oh.

18:19.743 --> 18:24.113
I guess that explains the bell.

18:24.148 --> 18:27.316
You know, I can see now why she loved you.

18:27.351 --> 18:30.253
I guess that's why she gave you that
figurine worth thousands of dollars.

18:30.287 --> 18:34.190
Our friendship was worth way more than...
what?

18:34.224 --> 18:36.959
Okay, people, can we get
back on track here?

18:36.994 --> 18:39.128
Riley, this is why we need you.

18:39.163 --> 18:41.697
Everyone falls apart without you.

18:41.732 --> 18:42.932
Everyone?

18:42.966 --> 18:45.968
Danny,
she's been there for you your whole life.

18:46.003 --> 18:47.670
Be there for her now.

18:47.704 --> 18:50.640
You don't understand.
I'm still mad about what you said.

18:50.674 --> 18:53.476
Well, I didn't mean to say
what I said when I said it.

18:53.510 --> 18:55.745
But once I felt it, I couldn't not say it.

18:55.779 --> 18:59.248
I don't know what either
one of you are saying.

18:59.283 --> 19:01.384
I'm saying she hurt me.

19:01.418 --> 19:02.518
I'm saying I'm sorry.

19:02.553 --> 19:04.554
And I'm saying get over it.

19:04.588 --> 19:08.057
Can you, Danny? Please?

19:10.460 --> 19:12.295
I guess so.

19:12.329 --> 19:14.363
Really?

19:14.398 --> 19:16.032
Yeah.

19:16.066 --> 19:19.068
I miss my friend. You need to come home.

19:19.102 --> 19:20.436
Okay.

19:20.470 --> 19:23.339
I mean, if that's what you all want.

19:23.373 --> 19:24.974
Wait, really?

19:25.008 --> 19:26.342
It worked?

19:26.376 --> 19:29.011
I did it? I did it!

19:29.046 --> 19:30.112
Yay, me!

19:32.382 --> 19:34.116
Mom.

19:34.151 --> 19:36.986
Uh, did you hear all that?

19:37.020 --> 19:38.354
I sure did, honey.

19:38.388 --> 19:42.024
If you hurry,
I bet you could catch a ride home.

19:42.059 --> 19:43.459
I love you, mom.

19:43.493 --> 19:46.162
I love you too, sweetie.

19:46.196 --> 19:48.164
I took all the candy out of your suitcase.

19:53.840 --> 19:56.742
Look, I just wanted 
to say I'm so happy we're back

19:56.776 --> 19:58.710
to being, well, us,

19:58.745 --> 20:01.780
and I promise I will not interfere
with you and Robyn anymore.

20:01.815 --> 20:04.817
Actually, Robyn and I broke up.

20:04.851 --> 20:05.884
You did?

20:06.920 --> 20:09.054
You did?

20:09.088 --> 20:11.790
It's cool. I'm dating Ashley now.

20:11.825 --> 20:14.660
Well, that was super fast.

20:14.694 --> 20:15.727
But, um, don't worry about me.

20:15.762 --> 20:18.831
I will not interfere with your love life.

20:18.865 --> 20:20.799
In fact, unless you need me,

20:20.834 --> 20:22.701
you won't even notice I'm around, okay?

20:22.735 --> 20:24.870
Okay. Were you able to get a new place?

20:24.904 --> 20:28.006
Yeah, yeah. The location is awesome.

20:29.876 --> 20:32.711
I'll see you around, neighbor.

20:35.748 --> 20:38.817
She rented it to Riley?

20:38.852 --> 20:41.787
Well played, Evelyn.

20:41.821 --> 20:43.055
Well played!

20:43.089 --> 20:44.923
Ah!

